> <OLD>
>
> Tucson transforms beside Vestige, and nodds in readiness to fend off the enemy insectoids. He draws up one of the missile barrels from his cab, and attatches it to his left arm. He saves the second for later, just in case it was needed.
>
> " Time for a little pest control, Prime style. All right Vestige, ready when you are, let's put these bugs in their place and get Rodimus back."

<NEW>

Vestige smiled again as he turned back to the insects in front of him,
laying down a tremendous amount of firepower!

Several of Vestige's attacks strike home, tagging the approaching
creatures on thier back and head. However these creatures seemed to be
built amost like tanks! Although there were a few burnt and blackened
areas on thier armored forms they still rushed foward to attack,
cannons on thier backs orienting on Vestige and Tuscon and firing in
return!

Meanwhile from behind the buzzing sound was getting closer, and the
room began to rumble a little more violently. The figure on the bed
bounced around, but otherwise did not move. The larger female that had
been knocked out earlier seemed to have regained consciousness and
with the grinding of gears she too shifted form and rushed in to
attack!

(TAG)

(OOC: I am unsure if Tuscon was firing yet or not. But if so, than the
attacks are about as effective as Vestige's)

Preston
